06/06/2023,748.705(b)(3) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,07/17/2024,07/21/2023,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium,No,"A 14-year-old, whom the operation had no time to build rapport with, was allowed to go to 3 stores merely 3 days after their elopement from the operation. During this outing, the child ran away again and took another child in care, an 11-year-old, with them.","A phone call was had with the Administrator. It was discussed going forward if a child elopes from the operation and the child returns, they will be placed on a safety plan. Discussed within the safety plan will be supervision and outing privileges. 

8/4/23- An in-person follow-up was conducted at the operation. A discussion was held with the administrator. She stated they still have a plan in place and will be implementing safety plans after a child has run away. She stated this will be done by a member of the administrative team. She stated there will also be a debrief held with the child and staff member following a runaway and if the child returns to the facility. "
